CRITICAL (Docker + Postgres init): When you define Postgres in `docker/docker-compose.yml`,
you MUST mount the DB init scripts so schema/seed load automatically:

- Mount: `../app/database/init:/docker-entrypoint-initdb.d:ro`
- Ensure database phase creates:
  - `app/database/init/01_schema.sql`
  - `app/database/init/02_seed.sql`
- If using a named volume for Postgres data, remember: init scripts only run on first init.
  If schema changes, you may need to recreate the volume (docker_down(volumes=true)).
</DOCKER_DB_INIT_GUIDANCE>
